  "id": "PLACE_the_brinewind_hollow",
  "label": "The Brinewind Hollow",
  "description": "The Brinewind Hollow forms a deep cavity cut into Darksalt Rampart’s columnar basalt, where evaporite seams thicken into pale ribs along the walls. The floor consists of fractured plates and salt-dusted talus, arranged in terraces that reflect the massif’s persistent tidal stresses. Mineral haze pools in the lower reaches, turning Saltharrow’s hard white spill-light into a stark, high-contrast sheen on glassy bands of rock. Narrow fissures in the back wall vent thin atmospheric currents that keep the chamber perpetually cold and abrasive.",
